I love this place!  Cozy little restaurant with the freshest seafood cooked however you like. Their sauteed shrimp-in-the-shell is delicious and very healthy when paired with a side of rice. Prices are reasonable for the effort it takes to make the food, the employees are friendly, and the mural on one of the walls is very charming.  Five stars!

Small place serving fresh fish in various delicious ways. You pick your own from the menu and they pick it up from the ice buckets and make them for you when you order. They had run out of the red snapper so I chose something else and it was very good. Prices are relatively good and the sides dishes are good as well. The staff is very accommodating and attentive.

You can get iced down fresh fish here. While I was waiting for a cab, I was admiring the way they displayed the fish all facing the sidewalk. I love fresh fish and know the tells of an older caught fish....cloudy eyes and of course the smell. It's rare that any fish store would let you smell the fish before you buy it especially if they're real busy. Anyway, I popped inside and bought some fresh salmon steaks. The owner asked me if I would like anthing steamed, pan seared or fried. I said not this time but I'll be back!

Delicious fresh fish! No frills, low key spot. You pick your fish and they fry or grill it to perfection! Coated with a splendid savory spice rub... Juicy, flavorful & moist inside and crispy tasty skin. Served with delicious rice, tahini, small salad & pita on the side. 2 nice sweet dates for dessert too. My big grilled Bronzino was $20 and totally worth it! Will be a regular guest from now on!!
